  "body": "A more robust version of the below code is here: https://github.com/markmiro/hardhat-ethers-network-confusion\r\n\r\n./package.json\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"devDependencies\": {\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\": \"2.0.2\",\r\n    \"ethers\": \"5.4.4\",\r\n    \"hardhat\": \"2.6.0\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n./hardhat.config.js\r\n```javascript\r\nrequire(\"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\");\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  networks: {\r\n    ropsten: {\r\n      url: `https://eth-ropsten.alchemyapi.io/v2/3RI0h7l9dI7NPpIWBKiASq6IV0cUFbRQ`,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.4\",\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n./script.js\r\n```javascript\r\nconst hre = require(\"hardhat\");\r\n\r\nasync function main() {\r\n  console.log(\"Network url:\", hre.network.config.url);\r\n  console.log(\"Provider url:\", hre.ethers.provider.connection.url);\r\n}\r\n\r\nmain()\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun on localhost network, and results look fine:\r\n\r\n```\r\n% npx hardhat run script.js --network localhost\r\nNetwork url: http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\nProvider url: http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, running on ropsten yields unexpected result:\r\n\r\n```\r\n% npx hardhat run script.js --network ropsten  \r\nNetwork url: https://eth-ropsten.alchemyapi.io/v2/3RI0h7l9dI7NPpIWBKiASq6IV0cUFbRQ\r\nProvider url: http://localhost:8545\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected**:\r\n`Provider url: https://eth-ropsten.alchemyapi.io/v2/3RI0h7l9dI7NPpIWBKiASq6IV0cUFbRQ`\r\n\r\n**Actual**:\r\n`Provider url: http://localhost:8545`",
